1.title: Pranks and Stunts
1.plot: Groups of people post the weirdest pranks, from lame ones such as PostIts all over the boss's office to mean ones such as an atomic wedgie given to an unsuspecting roommate with a car wrench. Individual - or group skills vary from playing a vegetable as if a musical instrument to an artful football ad parody, double-jointed contortions or freestyle mountain climber Dan Osman. Danger varies from street chain surfing to exercising while dangling at night from a 200 meter high crane without safety gear. Jackass stuff includes a life piercing on one's own tongue or '...

3.title: Celebrity and Wannabe
3.plot: YouTube is about the fastest way to some celebrity status, with or especially without actual talent. Some don't even know what they're doing, like a dentist-dazed kid, others would do anything, like swallowing excessive doses of spices or even a fatso stripping and waving his butt-crack into the camera. Yet genuine TV starts seek a second, uncensored career on line too, like Dustin 'Screetch' Diamond, now alias D-man, or accidentally star in a fluke scene. Some perform classical acts, like yo-yo, some do it so badly it becomes comical, other establish regular records....

2.title: All Things Weird & Wonderful
2.plot: Weird things include unusual animal behavior, bizarre record attempts and various idiosyncrasies, such as Japannese breast-feeding a cat. Some pull their stunts or gimmicks off so well it becomes wonderful, others are so lame it becomes inadvertently funny. Many celebrities now have a YouTube 'channel'. Even Bollywood produces parodies of Hollywood and other celebrities.

1.title: Epic Fails
1.plot: Many YouTube posts star unlucky 'heroes' whose endeavors go spectacularly wrong. Some arouse sympathetic pity, others rather seem to deserve utter ridicule. Some hurt only their pride, the less lucky incur serious damage. As video-cameras are everywhere nowadays, Murphys's law is recorded about as universally.

2.title: Animal Madness
2.plot: Animals do crazy things on YouTube, like a chinchilla licking a cat, a goose attacking a dog and his master in a boat, a barking cat, one that keeps playing a music teacher's piano, a skateboarding bulldog. A donkey mysteriously pesters a pants-down man in his meadow, an elephant abusing his trunk up a peer's backside. Some are staged, like a chained monkey driving a miniature motorcycle in Jakarta. Some are fluke victims, like an albatross killed by a golf Ball. Or of nature, like a couple of rhinoceros failing to mate or a drunk squirrel. Or of an over-weight cart ...

3.title: Ultimate Champions
3.plot: The race for Internet becoming ever more competitive, people strive for the most bizarre records, like greatest number of undershorts worn simultaneously, or really testing ones, like breaking concrete blocks or kicking one's own head. Some elaborate on sports, like freestyle football juggling. To others it comes naturally, sometimes it's mainly a matter of painstaking preparation, like lining-up for mattress dominoes. Sometimes a failed attempt is still funny enough to post, like a Japanese boy's rapid push-ups. Some amount to inventions, like explosive, Coke-based ...

4.title: Total Stunts
4.plot: YouTube shows thousands of stunts. Numerous are jumps and falls from, over or on just about anything and anywhere, with or without safety device, triumphant or painfully smashing on vulnerable body parts. Risks are just as real in para-sailing or on the ground, as with urban 'parkour' acrobatics or skateboarding, or even driving cars on an Indian circus ramp devised for motorbikes.

5.title: Rude Tunes
5.plot: Music(ality) plays a major part in countless YouTube posts. Some improvise 'instruments', like drumming on a mate's head, on school lockers or even band-wise using all moving parts of a car. Some write outrageous lyrics, or parodies. Some cleverly put music and/or (alternative) lyrics on non-performance scenes from real life. Other cases are about dancing or miserable failures to move musically.

6.title: Viral Ads
6.plot: YouTube contains many 'viral' advertisements, which gained sort of a cult following on their entertaining merits, even regardless of the product. Often they seem like ordinary non-commercial posts, one might rather compare those to product placement. Dverse types of stunts, humor and oddity are represented.

7.title: Rude Zoo
7.plot: YouTube has countless posts starring animals, some not the usual cats and dogs but other pets; draft animals and even wild beasts, in places ranging from zoos to homes. Some behave extraordinarily, like gorillas who dance or even walk perfectly erect, or a monkey riding on a piglet. Intrepid penguins jump from dazzling heights or even unto a huge predator, yet a rat on a subway arouses more frenzied reactions. Other are just cute, embarrassing like a swearing parrot, or more natural then people realize, like lovebirds evoking their name 'all the way'. Some look out of...

8.title: Cats & Dogs
8.plot: YouTube shows all kinds of animals, but the favourite pets species abound. Cats often show off their independence, initiative and individuality, whether alone or interacting, or just their athletic excellence and rarely failing instincts. Dogs, rather, follow or join, whether taught so or spontaneously, interacting with people or any other animal. Justice triumphs when abusive owners and other human fiends get their comeuppance.
